'''Khabar Arkhi''' ({{lang-fa|<U+062E><U+0628><U+0631><U+0627><U+0631><U+062E><U+064A>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Khabar Arkh<U+012B>'''; also known as '''Khabar Aikhe''' and '''Peyk<U+0101>n''')<ref>{{GEOnet3|-3070322|Khabar Arkhi}}</ref> is a village in [[Ali Sadr Rural District]], [[Gol Tappeh District]], [[Kabudarahang County]], [[Hamadan Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 949, in 188 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|13}}</ref>  

